user_question: What is the mechanism by which the venom of the blue-ringed octopus affects the human nervous system?
final_answer: The venom of the blue-ringed octopus contains tetrodotoxin, which blocks sodium channels in nerve cells, preventing nerve signal transmission and leading to paralysis.
